== Prep ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small
pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved).

Trim the @green beans{80}(trimmed and chopped into thirds).

== Rice and Lamb ==

When boiling, pour the @water{100%ml} into a large #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for
~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). When hot, add the
@lamb mince{200%g} and cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess
fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the rice has ~{5%minutes} of cooking time left, add the green beans to the
rice pan and cook for the remaining time. Drain the rice and beans in a
#sieve{} when ready.

== Lamb Rogan Josh ==

Once the mince has browned, add the red onion. Cook, stirring regularly, until
softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @rogan josh curry paste{50%g} and garlic and cook, stirring, for
~{1%minute}.

Add the tomatoes, @water{for the lamb} (see ingredients for amount) and
@chicken stock paste{10%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Cover with a lid (or #foil{}) and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the
tomatoes have softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Mango Chutney Yoghurt ==

Meanwhile, pop the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g} into a small #bowl{}.

Add half the @mango chutney{40%g}, season with @salt{} and @ground black
pepper{}, then mix together.

== Assembly ==

Add the cooked rice, green beans and remaining mango chutney to the lamb
mixture.

Mix well to combine.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if it's a little dry.

Divide the pilaf between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the mango chutney yoghurt to finish. Enjoy!